Detailed Description

Macro Definition Documentation

#define VPS_BUFFER_ALIGNMENT_RECOMMENDED   (32U)

Recommended VPS video buffer alignment for better DDR efficiency.

All application buffer address and line pitch could be aligned to this byte boundary to achieve better DDR efficiency because accesses split across 32 byte boundary would require 2 DDR burst accesses with burst chopping.

#define VPS_ISS_CALM2M_IOCTL_SET_DMA_PARAMS   (VPS_ISS_IOCTL_CALM2M_IOCTL_BASE + 0x0001U)

Set ISS CAL M2M parameters.

This IOCTL can be used to set the ISS CAL M2M dma parameters. This IOCTL should be called after creating ISS CAL M2M M2M driver instance

Parameters
cmdArgs[IN] const vpsissCalm2mDmaCtrlParams_t *
cmdArgsStatus[OUT] NULL
Returns
FVID2_SOK on success, else failure.

enum Vps_MemRotationType

This enum is used to define the memory data rotation and mirroring type. The rotation and mirroring is only valid if the memory type is tiler container mode. For non-tiler and tiler page mode, rotation and mirroring is not valid.

enum Vps_MemRotationType

Enumerator
VPS_MEM_0_ROTATION 

no rotation and mirroring.

VPS_MEM_180_ROTATION_MIRRORING

0 degree rotation with mirroring.

VPS_MEM_180_ROTATION 

180 degree rotation.

enum Vps_VpdmaMaxOutHeight

Output data max height.

This enum can be used to limit the height of the output data that is captured in to the user buffer.

By default HW will capture whatever active data comes from the external video source. The width typically remains fixed from the external source. However, in some cases external video sources may generate spurious frames of active data which have random height. This can cause user buffers to overflow if the height of such a frame is more that the allocated buffer height.

To avoid such buffer overflow, users should limit the maximum output data height. This a HW feature and limits that can be set are a few fixed values as shown below.

Any additional lines coming from the source are discarded.

Enumerator
VPS_VPDMA_MAX_OUT_HEIGHT_UNLIMITED 

Do not limit the output width, captured whatever is coming from the source.

VPS_VPDMA_MAX_OUT_HEIGHT_REG1 

Maximum height per line as mentioned in Max Size Register 1

VPS_VPDMA_MAX_OUT_HEIGHT_REG2 

Maximum height per line as mentioned in Max Size Register 2

VPS_VPDMA_MAX_OUT_HEIGHT_REG3 

Maximum height per line as mentioned in Max Size Register 3

VPS_VPDMA_MAX_OUT_HEIGHT_288_LINES 

Limit height to 288 lines.

VPS_VPDMA_MAX_OUT_HEIGHT_576_LINES 

Limit height to 576 lines.

VPS_VPDMA_MAX_OUT_HEIGHT_720_LINES 

Limit height to 720 lines.

VPS_VPDMA_MAX_OUT_HEIGHT_1080_LINES 

Limit height to 1080 lines.
